    id: 'pickleball-shoes-guide',
    category: 'Gear',
    title: 'Best Court Shoes for Pickleball in the Philippines — 2026 Guide',
    date: 'June 27, 2026',
    author: 'PickleSpotPH',
    excerpt: 'The right shoes make a huge difference. We review the best court shoes for pickleball available in PH — from budget to premium.',
    image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1769911111880-b9cc416dc03a?w=800&q=75',
    content: '<p>Can you use running shoes for pickleball? No — and here\'s why. Pickleball requires lateral (side-to-side) support that running shoes simply don\'t provide. Using the wrong footwear is the most common cause of ankle injuries on the court. This guide covers what to look for and the best pickleball shoes available in the Philippines across every budget.</p><h2>What to Look For</h2><ul><li><strong>Lateral Support:</strong> Reinforced sidewalls to prevent ankle rolls during quick direction changes.</li><li><strong>Breathability:</strong> Mesh uppers are essential in PH tropical heat.</li><li><strong>Non-Marking Soles:</strong> Required by most PH indoor venues. Check before buying.</li><li><strong>Low-to-Ground Feel:</strong> A lower stack height improves court feel and stability at the kitchen line.</li></ul><h2>Top Picks by Budget</h2><h3>Budget (Under P3,000)</h3><p><strong>Asics Gel-Rocket 11 (P2,800-P3,200)</strong> — The most popular budget court shoe in PH. Durable, good lateral support, available at Toby\'s and Planet Sports. Slightly narrow — size up if you have wide feet.</p><p><strong>Wilson Kaos (P2,500-P3,000)</strong> — Lightweight and breathable. Best for casual play. Found in select SM department stores.</p><h3>Mid-Range (P3,000-P5,500)</h3><p><strong>Nike Court Air Max (P4,500-P5,500)</strong> — Great cushioning with decent lateral support. Available at Nike PH stores and online. Runs narrow.</p><p><strong>Adidas Adizero Club (P3,500-P4,500)</strong> — Lightweight and fast. Excellent for quick hands at the net. Breathable mesh upper works well in PH humidity.</p><h3>Premium (P5,500+)</h3><p><strong>Asics Gel-Resolution 9 (P6,000-P7,500)</strong> — The gold standard for court sports. Excellent durability, superior lateral support, and great cushioning. Worth the investment if you play 3+ times per week.</p><p><strong>K-Swiss Ultrashot 3 (P5,500-P6,500)</strong> — Built for aggressive movers. Durable rubber outsole, solid support, but runs heavy.</p><h2>Pro Tip</h2><p>Replace court shoes every 6-8 months of regular play. Worn-out soles lose grip, increasing injury risk. In PH humidity, expect shoes to break down faster — rotate between two pairs if you play daily.</p><div class="blog-related"><strong>Related</strong><a href="../blog/pickleball-for-beginners.html"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Pickleball for Beginners</a><a href="../blog/best-paddles-compared.html"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Best Paddle Brands Compared</a></div>'
